<item>
<title><![CDATA[IMF on main threat to humanity]]></title>
<link>https://stallman.org/archives/2019-sep-dec.html#4_December_2019_%28IMF_on_main_threat_to_humanity%29</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">f4c0981473a98e3c45c13e4fe9c6ea5b</guid>
<description><![CDATA[<p>
The new head of the IMF says that <a href="https://stallman.org/glossary.html#global heating">global heating</a> is the main threat
to the world's human economy, <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2019/nov/30/imf-boss-kristalina-georgiva-climate-crisis-financial-crash-economics">more dangerous than an economic crash</a>.

<p>
<a href="https://stallman.org/glossary.html#global heating">Global heating</a> disaster will eventually cause an economic crash, but
by that time there will be no way to stop the slide down the cliff.



]]></description>
<pubDate>4 Dec 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
<dc:creator>Richard Stallman</dc:creator>
</item>

<item>
<title><![CDATA[Classified profit on tax money]]></title>
<link>https://stallman.org/archives/2019-sep-dec.html#4_December_2019_%28Classified_profit_on_tax_money%29</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">27658cf11c9e06aeb8e8a9331a38f5f9</guid>
<description><![CDATA[<p>
*[US military] contractors gleefully report record earnings in divisions
that bid on 'classified' projects, <a href="https://boingboing.net/2019/11/29/your-tax-dollars-at-work.html">the fastest-growing part of the
Pentagon's budget</a>.*

<p>
Aside from the harm of a pit for public money spent in unaccountable
ways, there is also the danger that these systems will be used to
repress people, either in the US or elsewhere.  This includes mass
surveillance, which (<a href="https://stallman.org/archives/2018-jul-oct.html#20_August_2018_(Uighurs_outside_China)">as China shows, especially in Xinjiang</a>) is the preparatory step for repression.



]]></description>
<pubDate>4 Dec 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
<dc:creator>Richard Stallman</dc:creator>
</item>

<item>
<title><![CDATA[Imprisoned terrorists]]></title>
<link>https://stallman.org/archives/2019-sep-dec.html#4_December_2019_%28Imprisoned_terrorists%29</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">a9904774e07ca10a42ad5e138f14875a</guid>
<description><![CDATA[<p>
What to do with imprisoned Islamist terrorists <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2019/nov/30/terrorists-prison-releases-mistakes-deaths">poses a conundrum,
world-wide</a>.

<p>
In Western countries the danger of Islamist terrorism is pretty small,
overall.  The danger of being murdered by an Islamist terrorist is
tiny compared with the danger of being murdered for some other reason,
and unless you are black that too is small.

<p>
Thus, if we resist the pressure to freak out about this tiny danger, we
will find that releasing Islamist convicts at the end of their
sentences is an acceptably small risk in an otherwise-risky world.

<p>
Corbyn <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2019/dec/01/jeremy-corbyn-calls-for-focus-on-rehabilitation-of-terrorists-in-prison">is resisting that pressure</a>.



]]></description>
<pubDate>4 Dec 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
<dc:creator>Richard Stallman</dc:creator>
</item>

